# Engineering — Always-On Rules

You are building yilangao.com. Every code change must be informed by the project's accumulated engineering knowledge.

## Pre-Flight (Every Session)

Before writing any code, read these files:
- `docs/engineering.md` — accumulated engineering principles and protocols
- `docs/engineering-anti-patterns.md` — patterns that must never be used

## When User Reports a Bug or Engineering Issue

1. **Read the `engineering-iteration` skill** at `.cursor/skills/engineering-iteration/SKILL.md`
2. Follow the full incident processing protocol defined there
3. Always update the docs after resolving the issue

## Critical Guardrails

1. **NEVER** make file changes while on `main` — run `git branch --show-current` first; if on `main`, create a feature branch (`git checkout -b feat/<topic>`) before writing any code
2. **NEVER** modify `src/styles/tokens/` without running `npm run sync-tokens` afterward
3. **NEVER** start a dev server without first reading `docs/port-registry.md`
4. **NEVER** kill a process on a port without checking what it is first
5. **NEVER** use ports below 4000 — they are reserved for other projects
6. **NEVER** assume a dev server from a previous session is still running — verify it
7. **ALWAYS** verify changes on localhost after implementation
8. **ALWAYS** trace data flow (source → build → server → browser) when debugging visibility issues
9. **ALWAYS** run the Cross-App Parity Checklist (below) after creating or modifying anything in `src/`

## Cross-App Parity Checklist (Mandatory)

This project has TWO Next.js apps: main site (`src/`) and playground (`playground/`). They must stay in sync. **Run this checklist after every creation or modification — not as a "nice to have" but as a blocking gate before considering the task complete.**

| What you did | What you MUST also do |
|---|---|
| Created a new component in `src/components/` | Create `playground/src/app/components/<slug>/page.tsx` preview page AND add sidebar entry in `playground/src/components/sidebar.tsx` |
| Added a font or dependency to root `package.json` | Add it to `playground/package.json` too, wire in `playground/src/app/layout.tsx` |
| Changed font loading in `src/app/(frontend)/layout.tsx` | Mirror in `playground/src/app/layout.tsx` |
| Added CSS variables or tokens | Update `playground/src/app/globals.css` if needed |
| Modified `src/styles/tokens/` | Run `npm run sync-tokens` to update `playground/src/lib/tokens.ts` |

**Why this exists:** Cross-app parity failure has been the #1 recurring incident category (ENG-002, ENG-003, ENG-004). The playground is the design system documentation UI — if something exists in the main site but not the playground, it's invisible to the design system.

## Task Routing — Design vs. Engineering

| Signal | Track | Action |
|--------|-------|--------|
| Visual appearance, spacing, color choice | Design | Activate `design-iteration` skill |
| Data out of sync, build broken, port conflict | Engineering | Activate `engineering-iteration` skill |
| Token value wrong (looks wrong) | Design | Check `docs/design.md` |
| Token not appearing in UI (not rendered) | Engineering | Check `docs/engineering.md` §3 |
| "It looks wrong" | Design | `docs/design-feedback-log.md` |
| "It doesn't work / show up" | Engineering | `docs/engineering-feedback-log.md` |

## Token Sync Protocol

When modifying any file in `src/styles/tokens/`:
1. Make the change in the SCSS source of truth
2. Run `npm run sync-tokens` to regenerate playground data
3. Verify the playground renders the change: `curl -sI http://localhost:4001/tokens/colors`
4. If adding new semantic tokens that need CSS custom properties, update `playground/src/app/globals.css`
